⚠️ 10. If connection terminates before completion, lock file prevents new healthcheck
Working with caveats.
The atomic lock (O_CREAT|O_EXCL) is correct ✅. PID-based stale-lock detection exists ✅.
⚠️ Bug — Stale-lock detection across machines fails: The lock file lives on the bastion at /tmp/cloud_health/hc.lock. The PID stored is the PID on the bastion. If the frontend reconnects and _pid_exists(owner_pid) is checked, it checks the local frontend host, not the bastion. Since this code only runs inside the backend on the bastion (the lock is acquired in if __name__ == "__main__" of backend/main.py), this is OK — but it means the frontend has no way to query lock status before pushing/launching. So the frontend may try to launch a 2nd backend and the second one will just exit on lock conflict. The user's spec is met but the UX is poor.
[PENDING] Frontend cannot query bastion lock status before launch; a conflicting backend will exit silently on lock conflict.

⚠️ Bug — Per-bastion lock, not per-cluster: The lock is at /tmp/cloud_health/hc.lock. If two clusters share a bastion (multi-tenant installer), the second cluster will fail to acquire the lock. Probably not your scenario, but worth flagging.
[IGNORED] Multi-tenant bastion sharing is not a supported scenario.


❌ 11. After all backend processes & SSH connections close, bootstrapper exits, browser stays open
Not implemented.
As noted in #4: the bootstrapper runs Popen() and immediately exits. It does not wait for the frontend, does not monitor backend completion, and does not coordinate cleanup. The browser tab opened by the bootstrapper is the credential prompt at port 9000 — which is closed by server.shutdown() at line 35 of main(), before the frontend is even launched. The frontend then opens its own tab at port 8080 in frontend/app.py::start() via threading.Timer.
So the actual behavior is:

Bootstrapper opens credential popup tab → closes it after submission
Bootstrapper spawns frontend → exits immediately
Frontend opens a NEW browser tab at port 8080 → stays open as long as uvicorn.run() runs (it never shuts itself down)

The frontend never auto-shuts after healthcheck completion — it stays running indefinitely. The browser tab stays open because nothing closes it. So functionally the outcome matches your spec by accident, but the bootstrapper-coordination part of the spec is not implemented at all.
[IGNORED] Bootstrapper-to-frontend coordination not required; browser tab remains open via frontend uvicorn — outcome matches spec.


